<inglise> Council Regulation (EC) No 2596/2000 of 27 November 2000 amending Regulation (EC) No 974/98 on the introduction of the euro </inglise>
<eesti> N&Otilde;UKOGU M&Auml;&Auml;RUS (E&Uuml;) nr 2596/2000, millega muudetakse n&otilde;ukogu m&auml;&auml;rust (E&Uuml;) nr 974/98 euro kasutuselev&otilde;tu kohta 27. november 2000 </eesti>
<inglise> THE COUNCIL OF THE EUROPEAN UNION, </inglise>
<eesti> EUROOPA LIIDU N&Otilde;UKOGU, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community, and in particular Article 123(5) thereof, </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa &Uuml;henduse asutamislepingut, eriti selle artikli 123 l&otilde;iget 5, </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the proposal from the Commission(1), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse komisjoni ettepanekut, (1) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Parliament(2), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Parlamendi arvamust, (2) </eesti>
<inglise> Having regard to the opinion of the European Central Bank(3), </inglise>
<eesti> v&otilde;ttes arvesse Euroopa Keskpanga arvamust, (3) </eesti>
<inglise> Whereas: </inglise>
<eesti> ning arvestades, et: </eesti>
<inglise> (1) Council Regulation (EC) No 974/98 of 3 May 1998 on the introduction of the euro(4) provides for the substitution of the euro for the currencies of the Member States which fulfilled the necessary conditions for the adoption of the single currency at the time when the Community entered the third stage of economic and monetary union. </inglise>
<eesti> 1) n&otilde;ukogu 3. mai 1998. aasta m&auml;&auml;ruses (E&Uuml;) nr 974/98 euro kasutuselev&otilde;tu kohta (4) s&auml;testatakse, et euroga asendatakse nende liikmesriikide valuutad, kes t&auml;idavad &uuml;hisraha kasutuselev&otilde;tuks vajalikud tingimused ajal, kui &uuml;hendus j&otilde;uab majandus- ja rahaliidu kolmandasse etappi. </eesti>
<inglise> That Regulation also includes rules which apply to the national currency units of these Member States during the transitional period ending on 31 December 2001, and rules on banknotes and coins. </inglise>
<eesti> See m&auml;&auml;rus sisaldab ka eeskirju, mida kohaldatakse nende liikmesriikide raha&uuml;hikute suhtes &uuml;leminekuperioodil, mis l&otilde;peb 31. detsembril 2001, ning eeskirju pangat&auml;htede ja m&uuml;ntide kohta; </eesti>
<inglise> (2) Council Decision 98/317/EC of 3 May 1998 in accordance with Article 121(4) of the Treaty(5) stipulated that Greece did not fulfil the necessary conditions for the adoption of the single currency. </inglise>
<eesti> 2) n&otilde;ukogu 3. mai 1998. aasta otsuses 98/317/1998, mis p&otilde;hineb asutamislepingu artikli 121 l&otilde;ikel 4 (5), t&otilde;deti, et Kreeka ei t&auml;itnud &uuml;hisraha kasutuselev&otilde;tuks vajalikke tingimusi; </eesti>
<inglise> (3) Pursuant to Council Decision 2000/427/EC of 19 June 2000 in accordance with Article 122(2) of the Treaty on the adoption by Greece of the single currency on 1 January 2001(6) Greece now fulfils the necessary conditions and the derogation in favour of Greece is to be abrogated with effect from 1 January 2001. </inglise>
<eesti> 3) vastavalt n&otilde;ukogu 19. juuni 2000 aasta otsusele 2000/427/E&Uuml;, mis p&otilde;hineb asutamislepingu artikli 122 l&otilde;ikel 2 ja k&auml;sitleb &uuml;hisraha kasutuselev&otilde;ttu Kreekas 1. jaanuaril 2001 (6), t&auml;idab Kreeka n&uuml;&uuml;d vajalikud tingimused ja Kreekale tehtud erand tuleb t&uuml;histada 1. jaanuarist 2001; </eesti>
<inglise> (4) The introduction of the euro in Greece requires the extension to Greece of the provisions on the introduction of the euro which are applicable in the Member States in which the euro was introduced when the Community entered the third stage of economic and monetary union. </inglise>
<eesti> 4) euro kasutuselev&otilde;tt Kreekas n&otilde;uab, et Kreekale laiendataks euro kasutuselev&otilde;ttu k&auml;sitlevad s&auml;tted, mida kohaldatakse liikmesriikides, kus euro kehtestatakse siis, kui &uuml;hendus j&otilde;uab majandus- ja rahaliidu kolmandasse etappi; </eesti>
<inglise> (5) For Member States whose currency is replaced by the euro after the date at which the Community entered the third stage of economic and monetary union, the definition of "nationl currency units" should refer to the unit of the Member State's currency as it was defined immediately before the introduction of the euro in that Member State. </inglise>
<eesti> 5) liikmesriikide puhul, kelle valuuta asendatakse p&auml;rast &uuml;henduse majandus- ja rahaliidu kolmandasse etappi j&otilde;udmise kuup&auml;eva euroga, peaks m&auml;&auml;ratlus "riikide raha&uuml;hikud" t&auml;hendama selle liikmesriigi raha&uuml;hikut, nagu see on m&auml;&auml;ratletud vahetult enne euro kehtestamist selles liikmesriigis; </eesti>
<inglise> (6) The provisions on the transitional period apply as from 1 January 2001 in the case of Greece, </inglise>
<eesti> 6) Kreeka puhul kohaldatakse &uuml;leminekuperioodi s&auml;tteid 1. jaanuarist 2001, </eesti>
<inglise> HAS ADOPTED THIS REGULATION: </inglise>
<eesti> ON VASTU V&Otilde;TNUD K&Auml;ESOLEVA M&Auml;&Auml;RUSE. </eesti>
